.TH "drm_fb_helper_fill_info" 9 "drm_fb_helper_fill_info" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
drm_fb_helper_fill_info \- initializes fbdev information
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" drm_fb_helper_fill_info
.BI "(struct fb_info *info "  ","
.BI "struct drm_fb_helper *fb_helper "  ","
.BI "struct drm_fb_helper_surface_size *sizes "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "info" 12
fbdev instance to set up
.IP "fb_helper" 12
fb helper instance to use as template
.IP "sizes" 12
describes fbdev size and scanout surface size
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Sets up the variable and fixed fbdev metainformation from the given fb helper
instance and the drm framebuffer allocated in \fIdrm_fb_helper.fb\fP.

Drivers should call this (or their equivalent setup code) from their
\fIdrm_fb_helper_funcs.fb_probe\fP callback after having allocated the fbdev
backing storage framebuffer.
